article_title: Natural Gas Sells Off as Demand Outlook Weakens
article_text:
Natural gas prices slumped Friday as weather forecasts into November warmed up, rolling back hopes for an onslaught of gas-fired heating demand with the onset of cool fall temperatures.

Natural gas futures fell 10 cents, or 4.2%, to settle at $2.2860 a million British thermal units on the New York Mercantile Exchange, its third losing session in a row. The market has been trading at its lowest levels in more than three years amid...
